## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="50020-103">En este ejemplo se crea un flujo de trabajo que consta de una única actividad <xref:System.Activities.Statements.WriteLine>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="50020-103">In this example, a workflow is created that consists of a single <xref:System.Activities.Statements.WriteLine> activity.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="50020-104">La actividad <xref:System.Activities.Statements.WriteLine> tiene un argumento de entrada <xref:System.Activities.InArgument%601> denominado <xref:System.Activities.Statements.WriteLine.Text%2A>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="50020-104">The <xref:System.Activities.Statements.WriteLine> activity has an <xref:System.Activities.InArgument%601> named <xref:System.Activities.Statements.WriteLine.Text%2A>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="50020-105">La aplicación host crea una instancia del flujo de trabajo y pasa una cadena, que se asigna al argumento <xref:System.Activities.Statements.WriteLine.Text%2A> de <xref:System.Activities.Statements.WriteLine> y es utilizada por la actividad <xref:System.Activities.Statements.WriteLine>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="50020-105">The host application creates an instance of the workflow and passes a string, which maps to the <xref:System.Activities.Statements.WriteLine.Text%2A> argument of the <xref:System.Activities.Statements.WriteLine> and is used by the <xref:System.Activities.Statements.WriteLine> activity.</span></span>  

```csharp  
Activity wf = new WriteLine();  

Dictionary<string, object> wfParams = new Dictionary<string, object>();  
wfParams.Add("Text", "Hello World!");  

WorkflowInvoker.Invoke(wf, wfParams);  

```
